5:
I understand... Yes. You can leave it
to us. Thank you for your help.
10:
...I suppose it would be best not to
keep Alk in the dark about this...
14: Why? Is something wrong with him?
19:
WHOA! S-Stella?! My goodness,
you've gotten VERY skilled at
sneaking up on people...
26:
...Then you might as well hear this
too. That man just now? He was here
to discuss the Voluntas Splice.
30:
But they finished it already. Did
something go wrong?
34:
No, no, nothing of the sort. Just the
opposite, in fact. There are plans to
hold an event celebrating its
completion.
37:
That sounds like a good idea. People
will be happy to hear that.
41:
There are apparently those who
want a representative from Starview
Village to attend.
44:
...Do you believe Alk would refuse
such a request?
48: No. I'm sure he would do it.
51:
You're right. He would do anything
he thought was in his power... But
this role would doubtless involve
politics—and that is precisely why I
can't approve.
54:
Given that I've put so much pressure
on him to make decisions, I feel it
part of my responsibility to help
lessen his burden. He's far too
swamped with work as is.
58: I agree. We should help him out.
62:
I could take on the role in his stead...
but I neither have the inclination to
act as Champion, nor do I think my
current form would be suitable...
65:
No, no. I should ask Regis. Few can
match his talent for underhanded
diplomacy.
70:
There must be something I can do
to help...
86: I'm going to be a politician.
90: I'm sorry, what? Did I hear you right?
93:
You're going to represent Starview?
Are you... sure you're up to it?
98:
Oh? Don't tell me—you were hoping
to reserve the position for yourself,
Alk?
103:
I see. So this is the path you've
chosen.
108: Yes. I know I can do it.
113:
...Then I won't try to stop you. I have
faith in your ability to represent
everyone in Starview.
116:
You need not even consider yourself
a "politician." Simply displaying your
unwavering resolve would be
enough!
118:
Meanwhile, I shall play the "mascot,"
while repelling whatever
disreputable scoundrels would dare
approach.
123:
In that case, shall I be your
counselor and offer advice from the
shadows?
140: When did all of you get here?!
147:
I think... I've been waiting for this day
my entire life.
151:
Give her the very best. I'll pay for
everything out of pocket.
155:
Okay, but please mind the overall
surface area of the clothing.
175: It should be illegal to be that cute!
180:
Perfection. Now THAT is what peak
cuteness looks like.
183:
What're you waiting for? Hurry up
and give Stella some
much-deserved praise.
188:
All right, we get it! She's cute! Now,
could you hurry up and pick a dress
already?! This is the fifteenth one
you've tried on!
197:
That's understandable. Everyone's
energy levels have been through
the roof. There were some pretty
intense dresses in there too... But
you seem to like this one, at least!
202:
The fabric surface area is a little on
the low side.
206: But I still like it the most.
212:
That settles it, then! I'm gonna go
plan the big reveal now! Oh gosh,
Nephtim is going to be thrilled!
216:
Whoa. I didn't even recognize you at
first, Stella. Looking good.
226:
Oh right. About your escort—here, I
got a letter from Albert.
230:
What's this? "Only with my death
could I ever atone for this failure..."
233:
"It is with endless shame that I must
impart upon you my inability to
carry out this most crucial task—one
which I was honored and humbled
to be offered."
237:
Uh, yeah. Feel free to skim the rest.
Basically, he can't do it cause he's
tied up with the Fang mercenaries.
I'll get Claw to talk him out of all that
"atoning with his death" stuff.
240:
Anyway, we've got plenty of other
people who could escort you. How
about Regis? Could have him put on
that white suit of his again.
254:
Is it okay to feel happy? And to think
this is fun?
257:
All I wanted was to help out. I never
thought it would enjoy it so much.
262:
Uh, yeah? Duh. Not everything you
do needs to leave you bloody and
bruised, you know. You gotta learn
to take it easy.
268:
Question! Is there any specific
reason you're not allowed to have
fun while doing this?
275: In that case... I will have fun.
278:
Alk. My vocabulary is lacking. I need
more words to express these
feelings... I keep saying "happy" and
"fun."
283: I'd be glad to teach you a few more!
